summary:
Since early age I have had a strong affinity with science, nature and geology. Early on in my bachelor programme Earth Sciences I came into contact with applications of geology in the oil & gas industry and found that this part of geology had a strong attraction to me.  During my Master programme I further focussed on this part of geology and gained valuable experience during several internships.

I joined the PGK and Society of Petroleum Engineers (SPE) and was active as a board member for the SPE Student Chapter Amsterdam. I have attend numerous lectures and excursions organized by the SPE Netherlands on specific E&P related topics.   

Affinity and experience with: petroleum geology, structural geology, seismic interpretation, well log interpretation, 3D modeling with Petrel (both reservoir and structural modeling), sedimentology, sequence stratigraphy.
